From 9da8ac827ddd65f94dbf574732027fd0aa58ac9d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thom de Hoog <thomdehoog@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:17:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Add optional Remote Control tab: TCP + MCP named-call server

Add a validated named-call control surface shared by framed TCP and MCP-over-HTTP.
Commands are allowlisted, strictly parsed, checked against live configuration limits
and fixed state-machine modes, and protected by a shared operation gate that rejects
competing mutations until real completion.

The integration is off by default. MainWindow gains four lines and Core a declared
session plus two delegating slots; protocol, validation, busy gating, the GUI tab, the
transports and the clients that call them live in three self-contained modules.
